cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network for person re-identification, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on optimizing the network for better performance, which falls under the category of machine learning, specifically deep learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category. The paper also mentions using four images as input, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper uses both verification and identification losses, which could fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cryptography and security (cs.CR).
